(144, 1, '2018-03-31 09:33:14', '2018-03-31 09:33:14', '<strong>Left ID:</strong>\r\n\r\n1. Proceed to the guard house in any SLU Campus gates.\r\n\r\n2. Report to the guard-on-duty that you have lost or left your ID.\r\n\r\n3. Fill out the logbook in the guard house then ask for a student pass slip from the guard. (The guard will then ask you for a collateral, which you will get back when you return the student pass issued to you by the SAO.)\r\n\r\n4. Fill out the student pass slip given to you by the guard and proceed immediately to the SAO.\r\n\r\n5. Give the slip to the SAO personnel-on-duty then fill out the logbook in the counter.\r\n\r\n6. Get your student pass from the SAO personnel.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Lost ID:</strong>\r\n\r\n1. Proceed to the guard house in any SLU Campus gates.\r\n\r\n2. Report to the guard-on-duty that you have lost or left your ID.\r\n\r\n3. Fill out the logbook in the guard house then ask for a student pass slip from the guard. (The guard will then ask you for a collateral, which you will get back when you return the student pass issued to you by the SAO.)\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Absences: </strong>\r\n\r\n1. Once a week subjects will have your classcard dropped after 1 absence.\r\n\r\n2. Twice a week subjects will have your classcard dropped after 3 non-consecutive or 2 consecutive absences.\r\n\r\n3. Thrice a week subjects will have your classcards dropped after 5 non-consecutive or 3 consecutive absences.\r\n\r\n4. Classcards will be permanently dropped after the 13th absence of the student.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Transferees:</strong>\r\n\r\nStep 1. Processing of Application - The transfer applicant shall apply for admission at the Students Affairs Office within 10 days before the start of enrollment.  Applicant shall submit the following requirements:\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Application letter with the following information:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>former school/s attended and course/s taken</li>\r\n 	<li>experiences in the former school/s</li>\r\n 	<li>reason/s for transferring to SLU</li>\r\n 	<li>course to be pursued in SLU</li>\r\n 	<li>reason/s for choosing intended course</li>\r\n 	<li>promise to abide by the rules and regulations of SLU</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>Certified true copy of complete academic records</li>\r\n 	<li>Certificate/s of Good Moral Character from previous school/s</li>\r\n 	<li>Six (6) copies of latest and identical ID pictures (2”x2”)</li>\r\n 	<li>Birth Certificate</li>\r\n 	<li>Police Clearance form hometown</li>\r\n 	<li>Transfer Credential (Honorable Dismissal)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Testing and Interview - The applicant shall undergo and must pass the Intelligence Test, Personality Test and Interview. The appropriate fee shall be paid to the Accounting Office.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>NOTE: Before taking the Personality Test and Interview, Foreign applicants from non-English speaking countries shall be required to take and pass the English Proficiency Test. Applicants who fail the English Proficiency Test are referred to the Institute of Foreign Languages and International Studies (IFLIS). To undergo a five-month English Proficiency Program. After completion of the Program, they shall re-take the English Proficiency Test and should pass the same.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>Physical Examination - After having passed the Personality Test and Interview, the applicant shall undergo and pass the physical examination at the SLU Medical and Dental Clinics after paying the required fee.</li>\r\n 	<li>Issuance of Permit to Enroll<strong> - </strong>Having complied with and completed all the requirements and successfully hurdled the tests, the applicant is issued a “Permit to Enroll” by the Students Affairs Office, he/she shall still be subject to the related conditions listed below.</li>\r\n 	<li>Enrollment - The applicant shall go through the official enrollment process as duly scheduled.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong><span class="a">Withdrawal from enrollment or dropping or changing of course,</span><span class="a">subject, or schedule is allowed:</span></strong>\r\n\r\n<span class="a">1<span class="l7">.for valid/<span class="l8">urgent reasons</span></span></span>\r\n\r\n<span class="a">2.with<span class="l7">in the pres<span class="l6">crib<span class="l8">ed time, i.e., within the first week of the </span></span></span></span><span class="a">semester / within the first three days of the summer term</span>\r\n\r\n<span class="a">3.upon <span class="l8">com<span class="l6">pliance <span class="l7">of the required procedure</span></span></span></span>\r\n\r\n<span class="a"><span class="l8"><span class="l6"><span class="l7"> </span></span></span></span><span class="a">4 .only <span class="l6">upon <span class="l8">appr<span class="l7">oval of the College Dean and other offices </span></span></span></span><span class="a">concerned.</span>', 'How to:', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '58-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-03-31 09:33:14', '2018-03-31 09:33:14', '', 58, 'http://localhost/wordpress/index.php/2018/03/31/58-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
